    "description": "Tokyo Printing Ink Mfg. Co., Ltd. manufactures and sells specialty chemicals in Japan. The company operates through four segments: Ink Business; Chemical Products Business; Processed Products Business; and Real Estate Rental Business. The company offers offset and gravure inks, inkjet inks, printing machines, and printing materials. It also engages in the manufactures and sells masterbatches and resin compounds. In addition, it offers plastic meshes and packaging materials and civil engineering materials. Further, it involved in the leasing of an office building owned in Tokyo and residence owned in Saitama Prefecture. Additionally, it provides dry colors; colorants for thermosetting resins; functional additives for plastics; compounds; detergents; powder resins; and functional products, such as 3D printers and radiation measurement. The company was founded in 1895 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan."
